Instead of this check here, can not we add similar check outside of the while (...) loop? For example replace:
if (buffer == null) {
    return null;
}

with something like:
if (buffer == null) {
   if (buffersPerChannel == 0) {
       return EMPTY_BUFFER;
    }
    else {
       return null;
    }
}

?
That way, we would avoid sending empty buffer if there are still more buffers in the backlog that are already enqueued?

